The paper deals with algebraic linear orderings, which are a mathematical concept related to algebraic trees and recursion schemes. This makes it likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the lexicographic ordering of a deterministic context-free language, which is a topic in Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). The use of algebraic ordinals and the Hausdorff rank also suggests a connection to Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper may also be relevant to Computational Complexity (cs.CC) due to the use of recursion schemes, and Graph Theory (cs.GT) due to the connection to algebraic trees.
